If the Gift Card Pin Field is active, you can define card number patterns here that should not be requiring a PIN. This might be useful if you have legacy gift cards in certain card number ranges that were printed without a PIN. If you specify anything here, specify it as a regex. Any gift card number matching this regular expression will NOT be required be accompanied by a PIN in the balance checker or billing page. Example: legacy cards that were 16 characters long and start with 1111 or 2222 should be excluded: ^(1111[0-9]{12}|2222[0-9]{12})$
